:::startTitle:::
Installation
:::endTitle:::


<b>Now</b> you can try ChronoJump&nbsp;<b>:::currentVersion:::</b> from any PC. This version is fully usable.
	<p>

	<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
	<tr bgcolor="#e6e6fa"><th>Operating systems</th><th><center>Instructions</center></th></tr>
	<tr><td><b>GNU/Linux</b></td><td>Install Mono, libgdiplus, and Gtk#. Read this e-mail: <a href=":::linuxMailDownloadLink:::">:::linuxMailDownloadName:::</a></td></tr>
	<tr><td><b>Windows</b></td><td>Read this e-mail: <a href=":::windowsMailDownloadLink:::">:::windowsMailDownloadName:::</a></td></tr>
	</table>
	
	<p>
	<h5>CVS</h5>
	<ul>
		<li>If you are an <b>advanced&nbsp;user</b>: from an operative system GNU/Linux, install <a href="http://www.mono-project.com">Mono</a>, download the Chronojump sources on the <a href="http://cvs.gnome.org/viewcvs/chronojump/">chronojump CVS on GNOME</a>, and execute <tt>mono chronojump.exe</tt> or compile with <tt>make clean</tt>, <tt>make</tt>.
	</ul>
	
<p>
Help can be found reading the <a href="http://cvs.gnome.org/viewcvs/chronojump/manual/chronojump_manual_es.pdf">manual</a> (spanish), subscribing to the <a href="contact.html">mailing lists</a>. We recommend you to read the <a href="faq.html">FAQ</a>.
<p> 
If you wish to know the advance of the project, please check on <a href="http://cvs.gnome.org/viewcvs/chronojump/changelog.txt">changelog&nbsp;file</a> (click the number at the right hand corner of "Revision").


